# Power Apps — keep specs in sync with code

Whenever you change **implementation** of a canvas app tracked in this repo, update the **authoritative spec Markdown** in the same change set (same PR or back-to-back commits), not only YAML or Studio exports.

## Which file to edit

| Area changed | Spec to update |
|--------------|----------------|
| Staff Dashboard: `PowerApps/canvas-coauthor/` (`App.pa.yaml`, `scrDashboard.pa.yaml`, shared app chrome, dashboard-only screens), or `.cursor-mcp-deploy/` for the same Staff app | [PowerApps/StaffDashboard-App-Spec.md](PowerApps/StaffDashboard-App-Spec.md) |
| Schedule screen: `scrSchedule.pa.yaml`, schedule-only controls, formulas, or `App.OnStart` / dashboard pieces that exist **only** for schedule | [PowerApps/StaffDashboard-Schedule-Screen.md](PowerApps/StaffDashboard-Schedule-Screen.md); if the change also affects the main dashboard or global app behavior, update **both** Schedule doc and [PowerApps/StaffDashboard-App-Spec.md](PowerApps/StaffDashboard-App-Spec.md) |
| Student Portal: `PowerApps/source/StudentPortal/` (any `.pa.yaml` or related source under that tree) | [PowerApps/StudentPortal-App-Spec.md](PowerApps/StudentPortal-App-Spec.md) |

If unsure, prefer **both** Staff specs when a change touches `scrSchedule` **and** shared app chrome or `scrDashboard`.

## What “written out” means

- **Behavioral or formula changes:** Update the relevant **step sections**, **copy-paste snippets**, and any **notes** so someone could rebuild from the doc alone.
- **Control / property inventory drift:** Refresh **Live coauthor control inventory** and **Audit findings** (or equivalent headings) when controls are added, renamed, or removed.
- **Tiny fixes:** At minimum, a dated bullet under the closest **audit** or **inventory** subsection describing what changed and why.

Do **not** treat YAML or coauthor files as the only handoff: the three specs above are the long-lived documentation surface for these apps.
